{"comments":"Pressure Types — Transfer curves and simulation for pressure input.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nPressure is a physical phenomenon with unique properties:\n- **Haptic feedback** — force feedback to the user\n- **Physical simulation** — resistance curves, spring models\n- **Hardware integration** — pressure levels, force sensors\n- **Robotics** — force-controlled manipulation\n\nPressureCurve is semantically distinct from ResponseCurve (Dynamics.Types).\nWhile both describe transfer functions [0,1] → [0,1], PressureCurve is\nspecific to the pressure domain and may be extended with haptic parameters.\n\nPressureSimulation provides pressure-like input for devices without native\npressure support (mouse, trackpad, touch without force sensing).\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude (Eq, Ord, Show)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[91,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[91,3]},"title":"Linear"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[92,9],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[92,3]},"title":"Soft"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[93,9],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[93,3]},"title":"Firm"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[94,11],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[94,3]},"title":"SCurve"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[95,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[95,3]},"title":"Logarithmic"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[96,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[96,3]},"title":"Exponential"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Pressure","Types"],"PressureCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[98,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[98,1]},"title":"eqPressureCurve"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Pressure","Types"],"PressureCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[99,54],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[99,1]},"title":"ordPressureCurve"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Pressure","Types"],"PressureCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[107,51],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[101,1]},"title":"showPressureCurve"}],"comments":"Transfer function mapping raw pressure to effective pressure.\n\nEach curve defines how stylus force translates to brush parameter changes.\nInput is normalized pressure (0-1), output is effective pressure (0-1).\n\n## Physical Context\n\nUnlike velocity or tilt, pressure involves force — a physical quantity\nthat can be measured, simulated, and fed back to the user via haptics.\nPressureCurve shapes the *feel* of pressure response:\n\n- **Linear**: Direct force sensing, technical applications\n- **Soft**: Light touch sensitive, natural media simulation\n- **Firm**: Requires deliberate force, bold/confident strokes\n- **SCurve**: Smooth transition, comfortable for long sessions\n- **Logarithmic**: Quick response, then plateaus (calligraphy)\n- **Exponential**: Builds momentum, requires commitment\n\n## Future Extensions\n\nThis type may be extended to include haptic feedback parameters:\n- Force feedback resistance curves\n- Spring tension simulation\n- Click/detent positions\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[96,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[90,1]},"title":"PressureCurve"},{"children":[],"comments":"All available pressure curve types.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Pressure","Types"],"PressureCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[110,41],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[110,1]},"title":"allPressureCurves"},{"children":[],"comments":"Human-readable description of each pressure curve.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Pressure","Types"],"PressureCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[114,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[114,1]},"title":"pressureCurveDescription"},{"children":[],"comments":"Mathematical formula for each pressure curve.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Pressure","Types"],"PressureCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[123,48],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[123,1]},"title":"pressureCurveFormula"},{"children":[],"comments":"Maximum sensitivity (derivative bound) for each pressure curve.\n\nThis bounds error amplification through the curve. Critical for:\n- Haptic feedback stability (prevents oscillation)\n- Consistent feel across pressure levels\n- Predictable behavior at edges\n\n| Curve       | Derivative           | Max on [0,1] or [ε,1] |\n|-------------|----------------------|------------------------|\n| Linear      | 1                    | 1.0                    |\n| Soft        | 1/(2√p)             | 8.0 (at p = 1/256)     |\n| Firm        | 2p                   | 2.0                    |\n| SCurve      | 6p - 6p²            | 1.5 (at p = 0.5)       |\n| Logarithmic | 9/((1+9p)·ln(10))   | 3.91 (at p = 0)        |\n| Exponential | e^p/(e-1)           | 1.58 (at p = 1)        |\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Pressure","Types"],"PressureCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[146,55],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[146,1]},"title":"pressureCurveMaxSensitivity"},{"children":[],"comments":"Debug info string for pressure curve.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Pressure","Types"],"PressureCurve"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[155,50],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[155,1]},"title":"pressureCurveDebugInfo"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[167,21],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[167,3]},"title":"SimulateVelocity"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[168,21],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[168,3]},"title":"SimulateDistance"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[169,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[169,3]},"title":"SimulateTime"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[170,23],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[170,3]},"title":"SimulateForceTouch"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[171,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[171,3]},"title":"SimulateFixed"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Brush","Pressure","Types"],"PressureSimulation"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[173,62],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Brush/Pressure/Types.purs","start":[173,1]},"title":"eqPressureSimulation"},{"comments":null